
# 🔍 Nmap Commands Cheatsheet

Nmap (Network Mapper) is the industry-standard tool for network discovery and security scanning. Used in Projects 2, 4, 7, and 9.

---

## 🎯 Basic Scans

| Command | What It Does |
|---------|-------------|
| `nmap <IP>` | Default scan (top 1000 ports) |
| `nmap 192.168.248.4` | Scan Metasploitable2 |
| `nmap 192.168.248.0/24` | Scan entire subnet |
| `nmap -p 22 <IP>` | Scan specific port |
| `nmap -p 1-1000 <IP>` | Scan port range |
| `nmap -p- <IP>` | Scan ALL 65535 ports |

---

## 🔬 Scan Types

| Command | Scan Type | Description |
|---------|-----------|-------------|
| `nmap -sS <IP>` | SYN (Stealth) | Half-open scan, harder to detect |
| `nmap -sT <IP>` | TCP Connect | Full connection, more reliable |
| `nmap -sU <IP>` | UDP | Scans UDP ports (slower) |
| `nmap -sN <IP>` | NULL | No flags set |
| `nmap -sF <IP>` | FIN | FIN flag only |
| `nmap -sX <IP>` | XMAS | All flags set |
| `nmap -sA <IP>` | ACK | Maps firewall rules |
| `nmap -sn <IP>/24` | Ping sweep | Find live hosts only |

---

## 🧠 Detection & Enumeration

| Command | What It Does |
|---------|-------------|
| `nmap -sV <IP>` | Detect service versions |
| `nmap -O <IP>` | Detect operating system |
| `nmap -A <IP>` | Aggressive (OS + version + scripts + traceroute) |
| `nmap -sC <IP>` | Run default NSE scripts |
| `nmap --script vuln <IP>` | Run vulnerability scripts |
| `nmap --script ssh-brute <IP>` | SSH brute force |
| `nmap --script http-enum <IP>` | Web directory enumeration |

---

## ⚡ Speed & Timing

| Command | Timing | Use Case |
|---------|--------|----------|
| `nmap -T0 <IP>` | Paranoid | Slowest, evades IDS |
| `nmap -T1 <IP>` | Sneaky | Slow, stealthy |
| `nmap -T2 <IP>` | Polite | Slowed down |
| `nmap -T3 <IP>` | Normal | Default |
| `nmap -T4 <IP>` | Aggressive | Fast, common in labs |
| `nmap -T5 <IP>` | Insane | Fastest, may miss results |

---

## 💾 Saving Output

| Command | What It Does |
|---------|-------------|
| `nmap -oN output.txt <IP>` | Save as normal text |
| `nmap -oX output.xml <IP>` | Save as XML |
| `nmap -oG output.gnmap <IP>` | Save as grepable format |
| `nmap -oA output <IP>` | Save in all three formats |

---

## 🔎 Lab-Specific Commands

```bash
# Full scan of Metasploitable2
nmap -A -T4 192.168.248.4

# Quick port discovery
nmap -sS -T4 --top-ports 100 192.168.248.4

# Save results for Splunk analysis
nmap -oN /root/scans/meta-scan.txt 192.168.248.4

# Find all live hosts in lab network
nmap -sn 192.168.248.0/24
```

